{"questionId":"12256","questionHtml":"<p class=\"indent1\" style=\"margin-top:12.0pt;\">A fourth plane with equation <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x + y + z = d\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>z</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>d</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;passes through the point of intersection. Find the value of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"d\">\n  <mi>d</mi>\n</math></span><em>.</em></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>(1.2, 0.6, 1.6) lies on&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x + y + z = d\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>z</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>d</mi>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\therefore d = 3.4\">\n  <mo>∴</mo>\n  <mi>d</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>3.4</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp;A1&nbsp; &nbsp;N1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"12256","referenceCode":"EXM.1.AHL.TZ0.35c","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"A fourth plane with equation x + y + z = d passes through the point of intersection. Find the value of d .","paper":"1","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.14—Introduction to matrices"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}